{"type":"message","id":"f1381cdf","parentId":"43d34df6","timestamp":"2026-04-30T19:19:30.702Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants to know what his total bills would be without the Affirm payments. Let me calculate the April total without the Affirm items.\n\nApril total was $1,620.17\nAffirm total was $255.42\n\n$1,620.17 - $255.42 = $1,364.75","thinkingSignature":"fb3215aad49f9d5cbe7378bc73d02222949aa3a1cacd04a547711db98bee03df"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nTaking the April bills total and removing the Affirm payments:\n\n**$1,620.17 - $255.42 = $1,364.75/month**\n\nThat's your new baseline without Affirm. Still got:\n\n- Xfinity Internet: $118.00\n- KUB (old apartment): $362.20\n- T-Mobile (2 of 2): $98.30\n- T-Mobile (phone bill): $196.59\n- Capital One Platinum Card: $25.00\n- Discover Card: $25.00\n- GEICO Insurance: $187.25\n- Capital One Quicksilver: $411.00 (balance: $261 after $150 paid)\n- Chase: $74.00\n- Apple Card Payment: $64.00\n- Citizens Pay: ~$74.52\n\nNice breathing room! 💪🧊💸"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":31494,"output":251,"cacheRead":224,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31969,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777576767623,"responseId":"0642de400011e3e46986a4c1e42bfac0"}}
