{"type":"message","id":"0c639554","parentId":"3ba74bc2","timestamp":"2026-04-30T21:14:41.434Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants the most cost-effective and fastest way to pay off their credit card debt. The most efficient method mathematically is the \"avalanche method\" - paying off highest interest rate first while making minimum payments on everything else, then rolling that payment into the next highest. This saves the most money on interest.\n\nLet me confirm I understand and get the info.","thinkingSignature":"96efb629ee412fb2a2b61ca18d2d4b5c90c332a1d12da7c7b8dcb9dcd55a4f9a"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nYes — that makes total sense.\n\nThe **avalanche method** is the most cost-effective. Here's how it works:\n\n1. **Pay minimums** on all cards\n2. **Attack the highest APR first** with everything extra you've got\n3. **Roll that payment into the next highest** once it's paid off — like a snowball gaining momentum\n\nMathematically proven to save you the most on interest and get you debt-free the fastest.\n\nJust give me the card details and I'll map out the exact game plan. 🧊💸"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":32183,"output":187,"cacheRead":224,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32594,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777583678588,"responseId":"0642f93e0f4c47239797b211e42e0941"}}
