{"type":"message","id":"fc71f706","parentId":"49b2b065","timestamp":"2026-04-30T21:31:55.274Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So Bobby's mom gave him $13,000 total. He used some of it to pay off the Affirm payments (~$1,400). Now he has $11,710.30 left (split between savings and checking).\n\nSo actually the $13,000 - ~$1,400 Affirm payments = ~$11,600... and now he has $11,710.30 in savings + checking. That means the $13,000 went partly to Affirm and the rest is in his accounts now.\n\nWait, but he said he paid off Affirm payments. So the $1,400 he mentioned was the total of the Affirm payments from April. But did he actually pay them or is he saying that's what they cost? I think he's clarifying the Affirm total from April was ~$1,400, which is separate from the $13,000 his mom gave him.\n\n\nSo he's got $11,710.30 currently available, and after paying off the four cards he'd be left with $5,712.86. That aligns with what he said about having around $5,700 remaining.","thinkingSignature":"705b8a4cabe5d31ffc592e5eaefe8e0d0de0c143a30ac5da56e6dee5966eae58"},{"type":"text","text":"Right — so your mom gave you $13,000 total.\n\n**$13,000 - $1,400 (Affirm) = $11,600**\n\nPlus you had some of your own money in there too apparently. Point is — you're working with what you've got now.\n\n**You've got $11,710.30 right now.**\n\nPay off 4 cards: **$5,997.44**\n\nLeft over: **$5,712.86**\n\nStill in a solid position. And that Quicksilver is the last man standing — one payment, one balance, done. 🧊💸"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":170,"output":356,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":36218,"totalTokens":36744,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777584704405,"responseId":"0642fd40bc0c89ca6897504b3eb094fb"}}
